&lt;p&gt;Th&amp;aacute;inig gn&amp;oacute;tha&amp;iacute; idir mh&amp;oacute;r agus mhion le ch&amp;eacute;ile D&amp;eacute; hAoine 26 de mh&amp;iacute; an Mheithimh 2009, sa Four Seasons Hotel, Droichead na Dothra, Baile &amp;Aacute;tha Cliath, &amp;aacute;it ar f&amp;oacute;gra&amp;iacute;odh gn&amp;oacute;tha&amp;iacute;, comhlachta&amp;iacute; agus fiontra&amp;iacute; a bhain aitheantas amach faoin sc&amp;eacute;im Barr 50 Gn&amp;oacute; le Gaeilge. Ba &amp;eacute; M&amp;aacute;irt&amp;iacute;n &amp;Oacute; Muilleoir agus L&amp;aacute; Nua a thionscain an sc&amp;eacute;im a thugann aitheantas do ghn&amp;oacute;tha&amp;iacute; agus do comhlachta&amp;iacute; a dh&amp;eacute;anann iarrachta&amp;iacute; an Ghaeilge a &amp;uacute;s&amp;aacute;id agus a choth&amp;uacute; ina gcuid gn&amp;oacute; f&amp;eacute;in, den ch&amp;eacute;ad uair i 2006.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Tugadh le fios do TalkIrish gur ainmn&amp;iacute;odh iad mar chomhlacht de na comhlachta&amp;iacute; a bheadh ar an liosta Barr 50 i mbliana agus ba phribhl&amp;eacute;id &amp;eacute; do TalkIrish do Michelle glacadh leis an ainmni&amp;uacute;ch&amp;aacute;n. Chuaigh Gear&amp;oacute;id Mac Eoin go Baile &amp;Aacute;tha Cliath chun glacadh leis an ghradam seo ar son TalkIrish.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bh&amp;iacute; An Seanad&amp;oacute;ir Mary White I l&amp;aacute;thair mar ao&amp;iacute;-chainteoir. Ainmn&amp;iacute;odh r&amp;eacute;imse leathan de ghairmeacha agus de thionscail agus ba dheas a bheith luaite ina measc ar an&amp;nbsp; liosta Barr Caoga. Ina measc bh&amp;iacute; seirbh&amp;iacute;s&amp;iacute; gairmi&amp;uacute;la, teicneola&amp;iacute;ochta, eala&amp;iacute;ona, na me&amp;aacute;in, miond&amp;iacute;olt&amp;oacute;ireachta agus l&amp;oacute;nad&amp;oacute;ireachta.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bronnadh gradaim speisialta ar chomhlachta&amp;iacute; &amp;aacute;irithe mar at&amp;aacute;; &amp;lsquo;Optinnet&amp;rsquo; a chuireann s&amp;eacute;irbh&amp;iacute;s&amp;iacute; bogearra&amp;iacute; ar fail do phr&amp;iacute;omheagrais Ghaeilge.&amp;nbsp; &amp;lsquo;Comhairle an I&amp;uacute;ir agus Mh&amp;uacute;rn&amp;rsquo; as an Ghaeilge a &amp;uacute;s&amp;aacute;id san earn&amp;aacute;il phoibl&amp;iacute;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ba iad Siobh&amp;aacute;n U&amp;iacute; Scannl&amp;aacute;in agus Bill Scanlon a ghn&amp;oacute;thaigh an Gradam Marga&amp;iacute;ochta ar son Fabraic F&amp;iacute;or &amp;Aacute;lainn/The Fabulous Fabric Company, Co Chorca&amp;iacute;, comhlacht deartha agus fabraic.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Samsung Ireland a ghn&amp;oacute;thaigh Gradam Gn&amp;oacute; na Bliana as an Tocca a l&amp;aacute;inse&amp;aacute;il anuraidh, an ch&amp;eacute;ad ghuth&amp;aacute;n p&amp;oacute;ca a bhfuil t&amp;eacute;acs Gaeilge leis&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;T&amp;aacute; an Iris ag cur s&amp;iacute;os ar an 50 gn&amp;oacute; ar f&amp;aacute;il le &amp;iacute;osl&amp;oacute;d&amp;aacute;il ag &lt;a href="http://www.events.belfastmedia.com"&gt;www.events.belfastmedia.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;ENGLISH&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Organisations and business&amp;rsquo; both big and small came together on Friday 26th June 2009 in the Four Seasons Hotel, Ballsbridge, Dublin, where businesses, companies and enterprises were awarded recognition under the Barr 50 Gn&amp;oacute; scheme. M&amp;aacute;irt&amp;iacute;n &amp;Oacute; Muilleoir and L&amp;aacute; Nua first initiated the scheme in 2006. The scheme identifies and gives recognition to businesses and companies who use and preserve the Irish language within their own business.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;TalkIrish was among those who earned a place on this year&amp;#39;s top 50 list. TalkIrish translator, Gear&amp;oacute;id Mac Eoin, went to Dublin and accepted the award on behalf of TalkIrish.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Senator Mary White was in attendance as guest speaker. A wide range of professions and industries had been nominated and it was wonderful to be amongst them in the Top 50. Services provided for range from professional and technical, artistic and media, to retail and catering.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Certain companies and enterprises received special awards such as: &amp;lsquo;Optinet&amp;rsquo; who provide a software service major Irish language organisations and &amp;lsquo;Newry and Mourne Council&amp;rsquo; for their use of the Irish Language within the public sector.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Siobh&amp;aacute;n U&amp;iacute; Scannl&amp;aacute;in and Bill Scanlon received the Marketing award for their company &amp;lsquo;Fabraic F&amp;iacute;or &amp;Aacute;lainn&amp;rsquo; /The Fabulous Fabric Company, Co. Cork, a fabric design company.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Samsung Ireland claimed Business Award of The Year with the launch of Tocca last year, the first mobile phone made to work with the Irish Language.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;The Top 50 magazine, which has a piece on each of the top 50 businesses, can be downloaded at &lt;a href="http://www.events.belfastmedia.com"&gt;www.events.belfastmedia.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="clear:both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://talkirish.com/aggbug.aspx?PostID=3378" width="1" height="1"&gt;</description><category domain="http://talkirish.com/blogs/sitenews/archive/tags/Barr+50+Gn_26002300_243_3B00_+le+gaeilge/default.aspx">Barr 50 Gn&amp;#243; le gaeilge</category></item></channel></rss>